Defendant Adrian D Watson in court with attorney Rosemary R Cuevas.  Chad Wozniak appeared on behalf of Tyrone St. Junior for the State of Wisconsin.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Court imposed one (1) year at the House of Correction, with Huber for work; credit for 5 days.  Good time allowed.  The Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with Cagney or Regina S. or their residence;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Anger management counseling;
 - Perform 50 hours community service;
 - Court imposed but stayed 60 days condition time, no Huber or good time, to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations;
 - Pay restitution to Cagney and Regina S. in the amount of $4,250.00 first before all other costs and surcharges; pay the DNA surcharge, costs, disbursements and surcharges.  Failure to pay any amounts would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
